# Summary of Findings: Changes to Common Baggage Fees Based on my research on the Delta Airlines website, I've found important information about standard checked bag fees and recent changes: ## Current Standard Baggage Fees For Delta Comfort and Delta Main customers traveling on domestic flights within the U.S., without a Delta SkyMiles® American Express Card, Medallion Status or Active Military exceptions: - $35 USD: For your first standard checked bag under 50 lbs. (23 kg), each way - $45 USD: For your second standard checked bag under 50 lbs. (23 kg), each way - Includes +1 Free Carry-On Bag and 1 Personal Item ## Recent Changes to Baggage Fees 1. **New "First Checked Bag Free" Offer**: - Delta is offering a limited-time promotion where the first checked bag is free on Delta flights - This offer begins July 16, 2023 - The offer is available for bookings made with a Delta SkyMiles® American Express Card - This represents a significant change, as previously the first checked bag cost $35 USD 2. **Medallion Status Benefits**: - Delta SkyMiles Medallion® Members already receive waived first checked bag fees as a benefit of their loyalty status - This includes SkyTeam® Elite & Elite Plus Members - Additional benefits may apply depending on Medallion Status and fare type 3. **Delta SkyMiles American Express Card Benefits**: - Cardholders can check their first bag free on Delta flights - This saves up to $70 on a round-trip Delta flight per person - For a family of four, this represents a potential savings of up to $280 per round-trip flight ## Additional Information - Baggage size must not exceed 62 inches (158 cm) when you total LENGTH + WIDTH + HEIGHT - Customers can check in and pay for bags during the 24-hour check-in window on delta.com, in the Fly Delta app, or at a kiosk upon arrival at the airport - The checked baggage allowance price varies by route and fare class ## Relevant URLs - Main baggage fees information: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/overview - First Checked Bag Free offer: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/checked-baggage/first-checked-bag-free - Medallion & Credit Card Bag Allowance: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/checked-baggage/medallion-baggage-allowance - Previous baggage fees: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/checked-baggage/previous-baggage-fees - Carry-On Baggage information: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/carry-on-baggage This new "First Checked Bag Free" offer represents a significant change to Delta's baggage fee policy, effectively eliminating the $35 charge for the first checked bag for eligible customers starting July 16, 2023.

      ## Current Standard Baggage Fees
      For Delta Comfort and Delta Main customers traveling on domestic flights within the U.S., without a Delta SkyMiles® American Express Card, Medallion Status or Active Military exceptions:
      - $35 USD: For your first standard checked bag under 50 lbs. (23 kg), each way
      - $45 USD: For your second standard checked bag under 50 lbs. (23 kg), each way
      - Includes +1 Free Carry-On Bag and 1 Personal Item
      
      ## Recent Changes to Baggage Fees
      1. **New \"First Checked Bag Free\" Offer**:
         - Delta is offering a limited-time promotion where the first checked bag is free on Delta flights
         - This offer begins July 16, 2023
         - The offer is available for bookings made with a Delta SkyMiles® American Express Card
         - This represents a significant change, as previously the first checked bag cost $35 USD
      
      2. **Medallion Status Benefits**:
         - Delta SkyMiles Medallion® Members already receive waived first checked bag fees as a benefit of their loyalty status
         - This includes SkyTeam® Elite & Elite Plus Members
         - Additional benefits may apply depending on Medallion Status and fare type
      
      3. **Delta SkyMiles American Express Card Benefits**:
         - Cardholders can check their first bag free on Delta flights
         - This saves up to $70 on a round-trip Delta flight per person
         - For a family of four, this represents a potential savings of up to $280 per round-trip flight
      
      ## Additional Information
      - Baggage size must not exceed 62 inches (158 cm) when you total LENGTH + WIDTH + HEIGHT
      - Customers can check in and pay for bags during the 24-hour check-in window on delta.com, in the Fly Delta app, or at a kiosk upon arrival at the airport
      - The checked baggage allowance price varies by route and fare class
      
      ## Relevant URLs
      - Main baggage fees information: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/overview
      - First Checked Bag Free offer: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/checked-baggage/first-checked-bag-free

      - Previous baggage fees: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/checked-baggage/previous-baggage-fees
      - Carry-On Baggage information: https://www.delta.com/us/en/baggage/carry-on-baggage
